Preconditions:
The input parameter `rectangles` is a 2D array of integers representing the coordinates of rectangles.
The `rectangles` array is not null.
The `rectangles` array contains at least one rectangle.

Postconditions:
The method returns an integer value representing the total area of all rectangles.
The returned area is the sum of the areas of all rectangles.
The returned area is calculated modulo `10^9 + 7`.